ZH: 我听到他的声音后愣住了。
EN: I was stunned when I heard his voice.

ZH: 他看到那个美丽的风景愣住了。
EN: He stood still in awe when he saw the beautiful scenery.

ZH: 她当场愣住了，无法回答问题。
EN: She froze on the spot and couldn't answer the question.

ZH: 那个小孩突然愣住了，似乎被吓到了。
EN: The child suddenly went stiff, as if frightened.

ZH: 在繁忙的街道上，我不知道为什么愣住了。
EN: I don't know why I froze on the busy street.

ZH: 他愣住一会儿，然后突然醒悟过来。
EN: He stood still for a moment and then suddenly realized.

ZH: 当他听到坏消息时，他愣住了。
EN: He froze when he heard the bad news.

ZH: 那个学生突然愣住了，无法继续做他的演讲。
EN: The student suddenly froze and couldn't continue his speech.

ZH: 当他看到漂亮的新朋友时，他愣住了。
EN: He stood still when he saw his beautiful new friend.

ZH: 她愣住了，好像被这个意外所困扰。
EN: She froze, as if troubled by this unexpected event.

ZH: 在他的临别时，我愣住了，不知道说什么。
EN: I stood still when he left, not knowing what to say.

ZH: 当他看到惊人的魔术表演时，他愣住了。
EN: He froze when he saw the astonishing magic performance.

ZH: 天色一黑，他不禁愣住了。
EN: It got dark and he couldn't help but freeze.

ZH: 我愣住了，因为我意识到我忘记了重要的事情。
EN: I stood still because I realized I forgot something important.

ZH: 在他面前的壮观景色前，我们都愣住了。
EN: We all froze in front of the magnificent scenery.

ZH: 当他听到好友遇到了意外时，他愣住了。
EN: He stood still when he heard his friend had an accident.

ZH: 接到那个坏消息后，他愣住了。
EN: He froze after receiving that bad news.

ZH: 她愣住了，好像时间在她身边停止了。
EN: She stood still as if time had stopped around her.

ZH: 当他听到这个可怕的消息时，他愣住了。
EN: He froze when he heard this terrible news.

ZH: 当我看到这么多人时，我愣住了。
EN: I stood still when I saw so many people.

ZH: 那个小孩看到雷电时愣住了。
EN: The child froze when he saw the lightning.
